Sentencas: Ni-Co alloy-based cermets have been characterized as alternative materials for the anode in hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ni1-xCox-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes were co-synthesized using a glycine nitrate process without further mixing processes.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both the electrical conductivity and the amount of carbon deposits were reduced by Co alloying, while the polarization resistance in H-2 atmosphere increased with increasing Co content.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode polarization resistance in a CH4 atmosphere also decreased with an increasing Co content.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These findings were strongly correlated with the carbon deposition behavior.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Co alloying was effective at suppressing the deposition of carbon and improving the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells that operate on CH4 fuel.
Titulo: Effect of Co alloying on the electrochemical performance of Ni-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 anodes for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells
